  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Chamundeshwari Electricity Supply Company Ltd. (CESC) versus Saisudhir Energy (Chitradurga) Pvt. Ltd. & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_8_1493_1515','2025INSC1034'); ><font size='4'> <strong>CHAMUNDESHWARI ELECTRICITY SUPPLY COMPANY LTD. (CESC)<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>SAISUDHIR ENERGY (CHITRADURGA) PVT. LTD. & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 1493</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1034</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006522025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KUMAR<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SATISH CHANDRA SHARMA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The following questions arise for determination: (i) the effect of respondent no.2/KPTCL&rsquo;s delay in commissioning the 220 kV evacuation system upon the timelines stipulated for fulfilment of the CPs and achievement of (ii) the entitlement of appellant to invoke and encash the performance bank guarantee in the facts of the present case; (iii) the sustainability of the finding of Force Majeure recorded by the State Commission in the absence of the contractual notice contemplated under Article 14.5 of the PPA;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 25-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 6888/2018</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_8_1493_1515','2025INSC1034',